ernments of Premiers Peterson, Rae, Harris, Eves, and McGuinty. He offers particularly trenchant analysis of the little-studied period following the Harris's "Common Sense Revolution," examining the implications of the 1999, 2003, and 2007 elections and their subsequent governments for Ontario's environment and politics. A timely, original analysis, Blue-Green Province should be required reading for anyone with an interest in the interplay of environmental policy, politics, and economic development in Ontario and across Canada.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aConstitutional lawzCanada. 0aEnvironmental ethicszCanada. 0aEnvironmental lawzCanada. 0aEnvironmental policy -- Ontario -- History -- 20th century. 0aEnvironmental policyxHistoryx20th centuryxOntario. 0aEnvironmental policyzOntarioxHistoryy20th century. 0aEnvironnementxPolitique gouvernmentalexHistoirex20e sièclexOntario. 0aHuman rightszCanada. 0aOntario -- Economic conditions -- 20th century. 0aOntario -- Economic policy. 0aOntario -- Politics and government -- 20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Environmental Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012z978311127716508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482238140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774822381423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774822381/original  a978-3-11-127413-3  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-127716-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  